 <text>
  <front>
   <head>SONG.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">TO those shades with delight I could fly,</l>
     <l n="2" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">How tasteless the town is to me;</l>
     <l n="3" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">In every gay scene that I try.</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">My thoughts they but wander to thee.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">Why remind me of those happy days?</l>
     <l n="6" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">Here is nothing but dress and vain shew,</l>
     <l n="7" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">Of those banks where I sung my first lays,</l>
     <l n="8" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">And remark'd every flower as it grew?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">Tho' we crowd the dull walks every night,</l>
     <l n="10" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">Where's the careless sweet ease I enjoy'd;</l>
     <l n="11" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">Not the beaux nor the belles e'er so bright;</l>
     <l n="12" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">On these shades are my thoughts still employ'd.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">Sweet shades! where with silence or — thee,</l>
     <l n="14" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">My mind every thought could approve;</l>
     <l n="15" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">Sweet shades! I admire every tree,</l>
     <l n="16" met="--+|--+|--+|" line_length="9">And I fly to the friend whom I love.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
